Rules:(Flex)
To use fles properties, use display:flex, 
in main div:

<div class"main_div">
<div class"child_1">child_1</div>
<div class"child_2">child_2</div>
<div class"child_3">child_3</div>
</div>

//size(equall width)
1. if we want all the child div of equall width: 
    then do
    flex:1; in all child div.
    .main_div{flex:1}
2. if we want one of the child_1 div double of other like 2:1:1: 
    then do
    flex:2; in that child div. and if want 3 times bigger than other child div do flex:3;  (3:1:1)
        .child_1{flex:2}
//order
2.1 if we want one of the child_1 div have width 80% then other and to make not squizing (ghatnu) 
    then do
        .child_1{flex: 0 0 80%;}
//order
3. if we want child_2 to come first: 
    then we do order like
    .child_2{
    order:1; or want in second order:2; or in third order:3;}
    
//Margin in between the div (column) like:
4. if we want Margin in between the div (column) in the child div: 
    then do
    justify-content:space-between; in main div.
    
    .main_div{
    display:flex;
    justify-content:space-between;
    }
    
    and in child div all child div
    do:
    flex-basis:30%;(10% for margin)
     .child_div{
         flex-basis:30%;(10% for margin)
    }
    or:
    .main_div > *{
         flex-basis:30%;(10% for margin)
       }
    * indicates that for all child of main_div(child_1,child_2,child_3) to make flex-basis =30%(10% for margin);
    
 
    
   //responsive_Part
 --remaining
 

5. if we want child div to : 
    then do
    flex:1; in all child div.


    

